Day 23 / 30 – SQL Challenge

Solved LeetCode Problem 1084 (Sales Analysis III).



Today I practiced using GROUP BY, MIN(), MAX(), and HAVING to identify products sold only within a specific date range.



Key concept: Filtering aggregated data using HAVING.



✅ SQL Solution



SELECT p.product_id, p.product_name

FROM Product p

JOIN Sales s

ON p.product_id = s.product_id

GROUP BY p.product_id, p.product_name

HAVING MIN(s.sale_date) >= '2019-01-01'

AND MAX(s.sale_date) <= '2019-03-31';







